<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Media General Inc.:
   Virginia Broadcast Company
   Names a Chief Executive
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS MEGA
</CO>
<LP>
   Media General Inc., a Richmond, Va.-based broadcast,
cable-TV and publishing company, said J. Stewart Bryan III
was named chairman, president and chief executive officer,
effective July 1.
   Mr. Bryan, 52 years old, is currently chief operating
officer of the company and publisher of its Richmond
newspapers. He will succeed his 83-year-old father, D.
Tennant Bryan, as chairman, and James S. Evans, 68, as
president and chief executive.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The elder Mr. Bryan and Mr. Evans will remain directors of
the company and serve as vice chairman and chairman of the
executive committee, respectively.
</TEXT>
